column18: Consent for participation in research  The purpose of this study is to investigate people’s perceptions of themselves, others, and outcomes. This form provides some basic information about the study. Please read the form carefully. You have the right to decide whether or not to participate in the study. The risks associated with participating are minimal, and no greater than those posed by everyday activities, like filing paperwork. In this study you will be asked to make some decisions and to answer questions about yourself and your life.  The survey will require approximately 15-20 minutes of your time. For your participation, you will receive $2 via Mturk. As a research participant, I understand that: a)      My participation is voluntary. b)      I have the right to refrain from answering questions I wish not to answer, and I may withdraw at any time without penalty. c)      The research is being conducted with the goal of publication in an academic journal and possibly presentation at academic conferences. d)     My responses are confidential. The identifiable information I provide, like my name or email address (collected for consent and compensation purposes only) will be maintained securely and will never appear in reports or papers resulting from this study. If you have any questions or concerns about this research, you may contact Oleg Urminsky at Oleg.Urminsky@Chicagobooth.edu or at 773-834-4710. If you have any questions about your rights as a human subject or are concerned in any way about the studies in which you participate, please contact the Social and Behavioral Sciences IRB Office at 5835 S. Kimbark Avenue, University of Chicago; http://humansubjects.uchicago.edu/sbsirb/; e-mail: sbsirbwise@listhost.uchicago.edu; or call (773) 834-7835. After you have reviewed the information provided above, please click the "agree" button below if you agree to participate in this online study.
